    "en": {
      "title": "There is a basic agreement on the IMF deal",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Reuters news agency says that Sri Lanka and the International Monetary Fund (IMF) have reached a preliminary agreement for an extended credit facility and an announcement will be made about this tomorrow.",
        "Sri Lanka, which is currently facing a severe financial crisis, has requested a $3 billion loan facility from the International Monetary Fund.",
        "Staff-level agreements are generally subject to approval by IMF management and its Executive Board, after which recipients have access to funds."
      ],
